description: Monday is the Met Gala, known as fashion's grandest event, where celebrities from various realms come together at New York's Metropolitan Museum of Art to celebrate fashion and each other.
title: 2024 Met Gala Red Carpet: Looks we love

description: The FAA says Boeing informed the agency in April that required inspections to confirm that the wings were properly bonded to the carbon fiber fuselage on certain 787 jets were not completed.
title: FAA is investigating Boeing for apparent missed inspections on 787 Dreamliner

description: Hamas said it has accepted a proposal from Egypt and Qatar for a cease-fire. It is not immediately clear what the proposal entails, nor what Israel's position is.
title: Hamas has accepted a cease-fire deal proposed by Egypt and Qatar

description: Madlib's music feels like a magic trick. On this edition of 8 Tracks, we bow down to Madlib's mastery, plus check out new music by Charly Bliss, Fana Hues and reminisce on an old Ted Leo record.
title: 8 Tracks: No beef, just a Madlib beat

description: Bumble, known for allowing women to message men first, unveiled new features that allow men to make the first move. Will the change breathe new life into online dating, and the company's stock?
title: Women no longer have to make the first move on Bumble. Will it make the app better?

description: The Israeli military on Monday ordered tens of thousands of displaced Palestinians in Rafah to evacuate, a move indicating Israel's offensive on Gaza's southmost area could be imminent.
title: Israeli army tells Palestinians to evacuate parts of Rafah

description: Morning Edition spoke to migrants hoping to enter the U.S. and the border agents tasked with keeping them out.
title: Is it easy for migrants to enter the U.S.? We went to the border to find out

description: Veterans who helped test nuclear weapons are fighting to renew a 34-year-old law meant to help compensate for the long-term health effects of their work.
title: Atomic vets are on the verge of losing federal benefits. Congress hasn't helped
